        title: "Wang Bi died at twenty-four",
        body: "The Chinese text in this book is Wang Bi's recension. He wrote the standard commentary at age 23. He died at 24 — possibly of an infectious fever, possibly heartbreak. Most chapters have outlived their best reader by 1,800 years. The age does not improve the commentary, but it does explain why a few lines feel hurried."
